    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5631/219: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-20T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 20, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Your 44, June 20, 4 p.m. Please inform the appropriate authorities that while
                    we welcome decision to send Lamping or substitute to Washington as early as
                    possible we should greatly prefer that the discussion at that time be not
                    restricted to preliminary conversations but be continued until an agreement is
                    reached. We should appreciate an indication also of what questions of general
                    policy in particular it is believed should receive further attention before
                    actual negotiations are begun. Incidentally, with reference to last sentence
                    page 1 of memorandum enclosed with your despatch No. 212 of May 7, 1935,<note
                        n="12" xml:id="d477fn12">Despatch not printed; see penultimate sentence in
                        first paragraph of memorandum, <ref target="#pg_584">p. 584</ref>.</note> is
                    the Netherland Government aware that 6 months of grace is calculated from April
                    1st not May 1st?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
